==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic, from Latin [[vicus]] ‘village’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[wik|wīk]], Old Saxon [[wic#Old Saxon|wīc]] (Dutch [[wijk]]), Old High German [[wih|wīh]] (in German [[Weichbild]]), Gothic [[𐍅𐌴𐌹𐌷𐍃]].

